description:
Department of Chemistry, University College of Science, Calcutta-700 009 

 Machigline (I), a new phenolic oxoaporphine alkaloid, isolated along with atheroline (II) and &beta;-sitosterol- \(O\) -&beta;-D-glucoside from the alcohol&nbsp;extract of the leaves of&nbsp; \(Machilus\) &nbsp; \(glaucescens\) &nbsp;Wight&nbsp;(Lauraceae), has been shown to be 1,2-methylenedioxy-9-hydroxy -10-m ethuxyuxoaporphine by spectral and chemical studies A fatty ketol characterised as a rarely occurring&nbsp;  \(n\) -hentriaeontan-10-01-16-one ( \(\equiv\) 10-hydroxypalmitone)(III)&nbsp;(first report of its occurrence in I auraceae) has also been isolated as an aliphatic constituent from the CHCl 2 &nbsp;extract of the plant besides the lignan and nor-lignan constituents The mass fragmentations of I&nbsp;and Ill have been delineated. The isolation of niachigime and atheroline constitutes the first report on the occurrence of oxoaporphines in  \(Machilus\)  species, and machigline adds a new name to the list of only a few phenolic oxoaporphines. 

 &nbsp;

